`,g.jsx(t.p,{children:"LCGs are fast and have low memory overhead, which made them the standard choice in early software. Their weakness is that the low-order bits tend to cycle with short periods — making them unsuitable for cryptography, though perfectly adequate for simulations and procedural generation."}),`
